# Database & Prisma Rules

## Schema
- Use `uuid` for primary keys
- Always add `createdAt` and `updatedAt` timestamps
- Use enums for fixed values (Role, ProductType, HomeworkStatus, etc.)
- Soft-delete via `deletedAt` field where appropriate
- Index frequently queried fields

## Prisma Client
- Single instance via `src/lib/prisma.ts` (global singleton pattern for dev)
- Always use `select` or `include` to limit fetched data
- Use transactions for multi-step operations
- Handle `PrismaClientKnownRequestError` explicitly

## Server Actions
- All DB mutations via Server Actions in colocated `actions.ts` files
- Always validate input with Zod before DB operations
- Always check authorization (role + ownership) before mutations
- Use `revalidatePath()` after successful mutations
- Return typed results: `{ success: boolean; data?: T; error?: string }`

## Migrations
- Use `npx prisma migrate dev` for development
- Descriptive migration names: `npx prisma migrate dev --name add_homework_status`
- Never edit migration files after they've been applied
